From 752460d1210d15ad68938252414c8b64849fad12 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vesa Kaskivuo <vesa.kaskivuo@iki.fi>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 01:55:50 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] fix: erase HRTB region binders instead of skipping in
 associated type expansion

When computing constraint sets for associated type resolution,
clauses with higher-ranked trait bounds (e.g. `for<'a> Add<&'a Self>`)
were silently skipped because `move_from_under_binder()` returns None
for non-empty region binders. This caused associated types reachable
through HRTB-bound trait hierarchies to remain unresolved.

Replace `move_from_under_binder()` with `erase()` in three locations:
- `compute_constraint_set()` for local trait clauses
- `compute_assoc_tys_for_impl()` for implied trait refs
- `compute_constraints_for_binder()` for inner binder clauses

This is safe because associated types are type-level, not
region-level, and `erase()` is already used at line 430 for the same
purpose. For non-HRTB clauses (empty binder), `erase()` behaves
identically to `move_from_under_binder()`.

Relates to #534, #967.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
