From 5dde23196795474760dc1ce14a37bd3e3571b627 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vesa Kaskivuo <vesa.kaskivuo@iki.fi>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 12:26:26 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] fix: unify SelfClause and Local(ZERO) lookups in
 associated type expansion

In trait method items, the implicit Self: Trait clause can be referenced
as either BaseClause::SelfClause or BaseClause::Local(Bound(0, ZERO)),
but these are stored as different HashMap keys. This causes "Could not
compute" errors when the key used at lookup time doesn't match the key
used at insertion time.

Two changes:
- lookup_type_replacement: try both SelfClause and Local(ZERO) as
  fallback when the primary lookup fails
- iter_self_paths: also return Local(Bound(0, ZERO)) entries converted
  to SelfClause-based, so constraint propagation doesn't miss them

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
