From 18ca0d0053c51122f56d72e20e7818208435c538 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vesa Kaskivuo <vesa.kaskivuo@iki.fi>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 13:41:06 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] fix: propagate implied clause constraints in associated
 type expansion
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

compute_trait_modifications() only propagated type_constraints from
local trait clauses (via compute_constraint_set), not from implied
(parent/supertrait) clauses. This meant constraints like
`Mul::Output = Self` on a supertrait were invisible to child traits
referencing the supertrait's associated types through an implied
clause chain (e.g., ExtConfig → ConstField → FiniteField → Mul).

Add a loop after compute_constraint_set() that iterates
tr.implied_clauses and merges each parent trait's type_constraints
into the current trait's constraint set, mirroring the existing
pattern for local clauses in compute_constraint_set().

Eliminates 86 "Could not compute" warnings for gf2 gfpn module.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../normalize/expand_associated_types.rs      |  21 ++-
 .../implied-clause-assoc-type-constraint.out  | 127 ++++++++++++++++++
 .../implied-clause-assoc-type-constraint.rs   |  17 +++
 3 files changed, 164 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 charon/tests/ui/implied-clause-assoc-type-constraint.out
 create mode 100644 charon/tests/ui/implied-clause-assoc-type-constraint.rs

